id: pmc-dfue
title: Bucket items by release field in full-history changelog
description: "Add release-field-aware bucketing so items with an explicit release: field appear in their tagged release section, eliminating duplicate Unreleased entries when pm update --release bumps updated_at after the tag was created."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: bucketing,changelog,full-history
created_at: "2026-05-25T20:48:11.269Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T21:12:31.725Z"
deadline: "2026-05-26T20:00:00.000Z"
assignee: claude
author: claude
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: Items with release field matching a known git tag bucket to that section; items without release field fall back to timestamp window; empty release windows are omitted unless includeEmpty is set.
parent: pmc-9mck
release: v2026.05.25
resolution: fixed
expected_result: items with release field bucket correctly in --all-release-tags mode
actual_result: items with release field bucket correctly; empty windows omitted; 31 tests pass
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pmc-9mck,related,"2026-05-25T20:48:11.269Z",null,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:11.269Z",claude,Replaces the previous timestamp-only filtering in --all-release-tags mode that misplaced items into Unreleased after their release field was stamped.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:11.269Z",claude,Adds optional releaseTag field to ChangelogReleaseWindow; release-context populates this when scanning git tags.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:11.269Z",claude,"Closed pm items typically get their release field stamped AFTER the git tag is created, so updated_at sorts them into the wrong release window with the legacy timestamp filter."
